16bool IsNonTruncatingMachineTypeFor(const MachineType& mt, const Type& type,
17 Zone* graph_zone) {
18 if (type.IsNone()) return true;
19 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Add more cases here.
20 if (type.Is(Type::BigInt())) {
21 if (mt.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
22 return type.Is(Type::SignedBigInt64()) ||
23 type.Is(Type::UnsignedBigInt64());
24 }
25 return mt.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer ||
26 mt.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
27 }
28 switch (mt.representation()) {
29 case MachineRepresentation::kBit:
30 CHECK(mt.semantic() == MachineSemantic::kBool ||
31 mt.semantic() == MachineSemantic::kAny);
32 return type.Is(Type::Boolean()) || type.Is(Type::Range(0, 1, graph_zone));
33 default:
34 return true;
35 }
36}
37
38void SimplifiedLoweringVerifier::CheckType(Node* node, const Type& type) {
39 CHECK(NodeProperties::IsTyped(node));
40 Type node_type = NodeProperties::GetType(node);
41 if (!type.Is(node_type)) {
42 std::ostringstream type_str;
43 type.PrintTo(type_str);
44 std::ostringstream node_type_str;
45 node_type.PrintTo(node_type_str);
46
47 FATAL(
48 "SimplifiedLoweringVerifierError: verified type %s of node #%d:%s "
49 "does not match with type %s assigned during lowering",
50 type_str.str().c_str(), node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic(),
51 node_type_str.str().c_str());
52 }
53}
54
55void SimplifiedLoweringVerifier::CheckAndSet(Node* node, const Type& type,
56 const Truncation& trunc) {
57 DCHECK(!type.IsInvalid());
58
59 if (NodeProperties::IsTyped(node)) {
60 CheckType(node, type);
61 } else {
62 // We store the type inferred by the verification pass. We do not update
63 // the node's type directly, because following phases might encounter
64 // unsound types as long as the verification is not complete.
65 SetType(node, type);
66 }
67 SetTruncation(node, GeneralizeTruncation(trunc, type));
68}
69
70void SimplifiedLoweringVerifier::ReportInvalidTypeCombination(
71 Node* node, const std::vector<Type>& types) {
72 std::ostringstream types_str;
73 for (size_t i = 0; i < types.size(); ++i) {
74 if (i != 0) types_str << ", ";
75 types[i].PrintTo(types_str);
76 }
77 std::ostringstream graph_str;
78 node->Print(graph_str, 2);
79 FATAL(
80 "SimplifiedLoweringVerifierError: invalid combination of input types %s "
81 " for node #%d:%s.\n\nGraph is: %s",
82 types_str.str().c_str(), node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic(),
83 graph_str.str().c_str());
84}
85
86bool IsModuloTruncation(const Truncation& truncation) {
87 return truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() || truncation.IsUsedAsWord64() ||
88 Truncation::Any().IsLessGeneralThan(truncation);
89}
90
91Truncation SimplifiedLoweringVerifier::GeneralizeTruncation(
92 const Truncation& truncation, const Type& type) const {
93 IdentifyZeros identify_zeros = truncation.identify_zeros();
94 if (!type.Maybe(Type::MinusZero())) {
95 identify_zeros = IdentifyZeros::kDistinguishZeros;
96 }
97
98 switch (truncation.kind()) {
99 case Truncation::TruncationKind::kAny: {
100 return Truncation::Any(identify_zeros);
101 }
102 case Truncation::TruncationKind::kBool: {
103 if (type.Is(Type::Boolean())) return Truncation::Any();
104 return Truncation(Truncation::TruncationKind::kBool, identify_zeros);
105 }
106 case Truncation::TruncationKind::kWord32: {
107 if (type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) ||
108 type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero())) {
109 return Truncation::Any(identify_zeros);
110 }
111 return Truncation(Truncation::TruncationKind::kWord32, identify_zeros);
112 }
113 case Truncation::TruncationKind::kWord64: {
114 if (type.Is(Type::BigInt())) {
115 DCHECK_EQ(identify_zeros, IdentifyZeros::kDistinguishZeros);
116 if (type.Is(Type::SignedBigInt64()) ||
117 type.Is(Type::UnsignedBigInt64())) {
118 return Truncation::Any(IdentifyZeros::kDistinguishZeros);
119 }
120 } else if (type.Is(TypeCache::Get()->kSafeIntegerOrMinusZero)) {
121 return Truncation::Any(identify_zeros);
122 }
123 return Truncation(Truncation::TruncationKind::kWord64, identify_zeros);
124 }
125
126 default:
127 // TODO(nicohartmann): Support remaining truncations.
128 UNREACHABLE();
129 }
130}
131
132Truncation SimplifiedLoweringVerifier::JoinTruncation(const Truncation& t1,
133 const Truncation& t2) {
134 Truncation::TruncationKind kind;
135 if (Truncation::LessGeneral(t1.kind(), t2.kind())) {
136 kind = t1.kind();
137 } else {
138 CHECK(Truncation::LessGeneral(t2.kind(), t1.kind()));
139 kind = t2.kind();
140 }
141 IdentifyZeros identify_zeros = Truncation::LessGeneralIdentifyZeros(
142 t1.identify_zeros(), t2.identify_zeros())
143 ? t1.identify_zeros()
144 : t2.identify_zeros();
145 return Truncation(kind, identify_zeros);
146}
147
148void SimplifiedLoweringVerifier::VisitNode(Node* node,
149 OperationTyper& op_typer) {
150 switch (node->opcode()) {
151 case IrOpcode::kStart:
152 case IrOpcode::kIfTrue:
153 case IrOpcode::kIfFalse:
154 case IrOpcode::kMerge:
155 case IrOpcode::kEnd:
156 case IrOpcode::kEffectPhi:
157 case IrOpcode::kCheckpoint:
158 case IrOpcode::kFrameState:
159 case IrOpcode::kJSStackCheck:
160 break;
161 case IrOpcode::kInt32Constant: {
162 // NOTE: Constants require special handling as they are shared between
163 // machine graphs and non-machine graphs lowered during SL. The former
164 // might have assigned Type::Machine() to the constant, but to be able
165 // to provide a different type for uses of constants that don't come
166 // from machine graphs, the machine-uses of Int32Constants have been
167 // put behind additional SLVerifierHints to provide the required
168 // Type::Machine() to them, such that we can treat constants here as
169 // having JS types to satisfy their non-machine uses.
170 int32_t value = OpParameter<int32_t>(node->op());
171 Type type = Type::Constant(value, graph_zone());
172 SetType(node, type);
173 SetTruncation(node, GeneralizeTruncation(Truncation::Word32(), type));
174 break;
175 }
176 case IrOpcode::kInt64Constant:
177 case IrOpcode::kFloat64Constant: {
178 // Constants might be untyped, because they are cached in the graph and
179 // used in different contexts such that no single type can be assigned.
180 // Their type is provided by an introduced TypeGuard where necessary.
181 break;
182 }
183 case IrOpcode::kHeapConstant:
184 break;
185 case IrOpcode::kCheckedFloat64ToInt32: {
186 Type input_type = InputType(node, 0);
187 DCHECK(input_type.Is(Type::Number()));
188
189 const auto& p = CheckMinusZeroParametersOf(node->op());
190 if (p.mode() == CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero) {
191 // Remove -0 from input_type.
192 input_type =
193 Type::Intersect(input_type, Type::Signed32(), graph_zone());
194 } else {
195 input_type = Type::Intersect(input_type, Type::Signed32OrMinusZero(),
196 graph_zone());
197 }
198 CheckAndSet(node, input_type, Truncation::Word32());
199 break;
200 }
201 case IrOpcode::kCheckedTaggedToTaggedSigned: {
202 Type input_type = InputType(node, 0);
203 Type output_type =
204 Type::Intersect(input_type, Type::SignedSmall(), graph_zone());
205 Truncation output_trunc = InputTruncation(node, 0);
206 CheckAndSet(node, output_type, output_trunc);
207 break;
208 }
209 case IrOpcode::kCheckedTaggedToTaggedPointer:
210 CheckAndSet(node, InputType(node, 0), InputTruncation(node, 0));
211 break;
212 case IrOpcode::kTruncateTaggedToBit: {
213 Type input_type = InputType(node, 0);
214 Truncation input_trunc = InputTruncation(node, 0);
215 // Cannot have other truncation here, because identified values lead to
216 // different results when converted to bit.
217 CHECK(input_trunc == Truncation::Bool() ||
218 input_trunc == Truncation::Any());
219 Type output_type = op_typer.ToBoolean(input_type);
220 CheckAndSet(node, output_type, Truncation::Bool());
221 break;
222 }
223 case IrOpcode::kInt32Add: {
224 Type left_type = InputType(node, 0);
225 Type right_type = InputType(node, 1);
226 Type output_type;
227 if (left_type.IsNone() && right_type.IsNone()) {
228 output_type = Type::None();
229 } else if (left_type.Is(Type::Machine()) &&
230 right_type.Is(Type::Machine())) {
231 output_type = Type::Machine();
232 } else if (left_type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball()) &&
233 right_type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
234 left_type = op_typer.ToNumber(left_type);
235 right_type = op_typer.ToNumber(right_type);
236 output_type = op_typer.NumberAdd(left_type, right_type);
237 } else {
238 ReportInvalidTypeCombination(node, {left_type, right_type});
239 }
240 Truncation output_trunc =
241 JoinTruncation(InputTruncation(node, 0), InputTruncation(node, 1),
242 Truncation::Word32());
243 CHECK(IsModuloTruncation(output_trunc));
244 CheckAndSet(node, output_type, output_trunc);
245 break;
246 }
247 case IrOpcode::kInt32Sub: {
248 Type left_type = InputType(node, 0);
249 Type right_type = InputType(node, 1);
250 Type output_type;
251 if (left_type.IsNone() && right_type.IsNone()) {
252 output_type = Type::None();
253 } else if (left_type.Is(Type::Machine()) &&
254 right_type.Is(Type::Machine())) {
255 output_type = Type::Machine();
256 } else if (left_type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball()) &&
257 right_type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
258 left_type = op_typer.ToNumber(left_type);
259 right_type = op_typer.ToNumber(right_type);
260 output_type = op_typer.NumberSubtract(left_type, right_type);
261 } else {
262 ReportInvalidTypeCombination(node, {left_type, right_type});
263 }
264 Truncation output_trunc =
265 JoinTruncation(InputTruncation(node, 0), InputTruncation(node, 1),
266 Truncation::Word32());
267 CHECK(IsModuloTruncation(output_trunc));
268 CheckAndSet(node, output_type, output_trunc);
269 break;
270 }
271 case IrOpcode::kChangeInt31ToTaggedSigned:
272 case IrOpcode::kChangeInt32ToTagged:
273 case IrOpcode::kChangeFloat32ToFloat64:
274 case IrOpcode::kChangeInt32ToInt64:
275 case IrOpcode::kChangeUint32ToUint64:
276 case IrOpcode::kChangeUint64ToTagged: {
277 // These change operators do not truncate any values and can simply
278 // forward input type and truncation.
279 CheckAndSet(node, InputType(node, 0), InputTruncation(node, 0));
280 break;
281 }
282 case IrOpcode::kChangeFloat64ToInt64: {
283 Truncation output_trunc =
284 JoinTruncation(InputTruncation(node, 0), Truncation::Word64());
285 CheckAndSet(node, InputType(node, 0), output_trunc);
286 break;
287 }
288 case IrOpcode::kInt64Add: {
289 Type left_type = InputType(node, 0);
290 Type right_type = InputType(node, 1);
291 Type output_type;
292 if (left_type.IsNone() && right_type.IsNone()) {
293 // None x None -> None
294 output_type = Type::None();
295 } else if (left_type.Is(Type::Machine()) &&
296 right_type.Is(Type::Machine())) {
297 // Machine x Machine -> Machine
298 output_type = Type::Machine();
299 } else if (left_type.Is(Type::BigInt()) &&
300 right_type.Is(Type::BigInt())) {
301 // BigInt x BigInt -> BigInt
302 output_type = op_typer.BigIntAdd(left_type, right_type);
303 } else if (left_type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball()) &&
304 right_type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
305 // Number x Number -> Number
306 left_type = op_typer.ToNumber(left_type);
307 right_type = op_typer.ToNumber(right_type);
308 output_type = op_typer.NumberAdd(left_type, right_type);
309 } else {
310 // Invalid type combination.
311 ReportInvalidTypeCombination(node, {left_type, right_type});
312 }
313 Truncation output_trunc =
314 JoinTruncation(InputTruncation(node, 0), InputTruncation(node, 1),
315 Truncation::Word64());
316 CHECK(IsModuloTruncation(output_trunc));
317 CheckAndSet(node, output_type, output_trunc);
318 break;
319 }
320 case IrOpcode::kInt64Sub: {
321 Type left_type = InputType(node, 0);
322 Type right_type = InputType(node, 1);
323 Type output_type;
324 if (left_type.IsNone() && right_type.IsNone()) {
325 // None x None -> None
326 output_type = Type::None();
327 } else if (left_type.Is(Type::Machine()) &&
328 right_type.Is(Type::Machine())) {
329 // Machine x Machine -> Machine
330 output_type = Type::Machine();
331 } else if (left_type.Is(Type::BigInt()) &&
332 right_type.Is(Type::BigInt())) {
333 // BigInt x BigInt -> BigInt
334 output_type = op_typer.BigIntSubtract(left_type, right_type);
335 } else if (left_type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball()) &&
336 right_type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
337 // Number x Number -> Number
338 left_type = op_typer.ToNumber(left_type);
339 right_type = op_typer.ToNumber(right_type);
340 output_type = op_typer.NumberSubtract(left_type, right_type);
341 } else {
342 // Invalid type combination.
343 ReportInvalidTypeCombination(node, {left_type, right_type});
344 }
345 Truncation output_trunc =
346 JoinTruncation(InputTruncation(node, 0), InputTruncation(node, 1),
347 Truncation::Word64());
348 CHECK(IsModuloTruncation(output_trunc));
349 CheckAndSet(node, output_type, output_trunc);
350 break;
351 }
352 case IrOpcode::kDeadValue: {
353 CheckAndSet(node, Type::None(), Truncation::Any());
354 break;
355 }
356 case IrOpcode::kTypeGuard: {
357 Type output_type = op_typer.TypeTypeGuard(node->op(), InputType(node, 0));
358 // TypeGuard has no effect on trunction, but the restricted type may help
359 // generalize it.
360 CheckAndSet(node, output_type, InputTruncation(node, 0));
361 break;
362 }
363 case IrOpcode::kTruncateBigIntToWord64: {
364 Type input_type = InputType(node, 0);
365 CHECK(input_type.Is(Type::BigInt()));
366 CHECK(Truncation::Word64().IsLessGeneralThan(InputTruncation(node, 0)));
367 CheckAndSet(node, input_type, Truncation::Word64());
368 break;
369 }
370 case IrOpcode::kChangeTaggedSignedToInt64: {
371 Type input_type = InputType(node, 0);
372 CHECK(input_type.Is(Type::Number()));
373 Truncation output_trunc =
374 JoinTruncation(InputTruncation(node, 0), Truncation::Word64());
375 CheckAndSet(node, input_type, output_trunc);
376 break;
377 }
378 case IrOpcode::kCheckBigInt: {
379 Type input_type = InputType(node, 0);
380 input_type = Type::Intersect(input_type, Type::BigInt(), graph_zone());
381 CheckAndSet(node, input_type, InputTruncation(node, 0));
382 break;
383 }
384 case IrOpcode::kCheckedBigIntToBigInt64: {
385 Type input_type = InputType(node, 0);
386 CHECK(input_type.Is(Type::BigInt()));
387 input_type =
388 Type::Intersect(input_type, Type::SignedBigInt64(), graph_zone());
389 CheckAndSet(node, input_type, InputTruncation(node, 0));
390 break;
391 }
392 case IrOpcode::kReturn: {
393 const int return_value_count = ValueInputCountOfReturn(node->op());
394 for (int i = 0; i < return_value_count; ++i) {
395 Type input_type = InputType(node, 1 + i);
396 Truncation input_trunc = InputTruncation(node, 1 + i);
397 input_trunc = GeneralizeTruncation(input_trunc, input_type);
398 // No values must be lost due to truncation.
399 CHECK_EQ(input_trunc, Truncation::Any());
400 }
401 break;
402 }
403 case IrOpcode::kSLVerifierHint: {
404 Type output_type = InputType(node, 0);
405 Truncation output_trunc = InputTruncation(node, 0);
406 const auto& p = SLVerifierHintParametersOf(node->op());
407
408 if (const Operator* semantics = p.semantics()) {
409 switch (semantics->opcode()) {
410 case IrOpcode::kPlainPrimitiveToNumber:
411 output_type = op_typer.ToNumber(output_type);
412 break;
413 default:
414 UNREACHABLE();
415 }
416 }
417
418 if (p.override_output_type()) {
419 output_type = *p.override_output_type();
420 }
421
422 SetType(node, output_type);
423 SetTruncation(node, GeneralizeTruncation(output_trunc, output_type));
424 break;
425 }
426 case IrOpcode::kBranch: {
427 CHECK_EQ(BranchParametersOf(node->op()).semantics(),
428 BranchSemantics::kMachine);
429 Type input_type = InputType(node, 0);
430 CHECK(input_type.Is(Type::Boolean()) || input_type.Is(Type::Machine()));
431 break;
432 }
433 case IrOpcode::kTypedStateValues: {
434 const ZoneVector<MachineType>* machine_types = MachineTypesOf(node->op());
435 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(machine_types->size()); ++i) {
436 // Inputs must not be truncated.
437 CHECK_EQ(InputTruncation(node, i), Truncation::Any());
438 CHECK(IsNonTruncatingMachineTypeFor(machine_types->at(i),
439 InputType(node, i), graph_zone()));
440 }
441 break;
442 }
443 case IrOpcode::kParameter: {
444 CHECK(NodeProperties::IsTyped(node));
445 SetTruncation(node, Truncation::Any());
446 break;
447 }
448 case IrOpcode::kEnterMachineGraph:
449 case IrOpcode::kExitMachineGraph: {
450 // Eliminated during lowering.
451 UNREACHABLE();
452 }
